  "prompt": "Is morning sickness a sign of good pregnancy?",
  "response": "Morning sickness is a common symptom during pregnancy and typically refers to nausea and vomiting that occurs, often in the morning, especially during the first trimester. It is generally considered a normal part of pregnancy and is thought to be related to hormonal changes, specifically the rise in human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG). While it can be unpleasant, experiencing morning sickness is often seen as an indication that the pregnancy is progressing normally.\n\nHowever, it is essential to note that not experiencing morning sickness does not necessarily indicate a problem with the pregnancy. Some women may have mild symptoms or none at all and still go on to have healthy pregnancies.\n\nIf morning sickness becomes severe (a condition known as hyperemesis gravidarum), it can lead to dehydration and malnutrition, and you should seek medical attention. Always consult with a healthcare provider for any concerns about symptoms during pregnancy.",
